SECTION 3 — FEATURES

Section title: "Everything You Need to Compete at Your Best"
Section sub: "Purpose-built tools for serious barrel racers."

Six feature cards in a 3-column grid (2-column on tablet, 1-column mobile). Each card has an icon, title, and 2-line description. Cards use #1F2937 background, rounded corners, subtle amber icon.

Feature cards:
1. Icon: stopwatch — "Run Logging" — "Log every run with time, barrel status, payout, and media in seconds."
2. Icon: horse / star — "Horse Profiles" — "Track each horse's personal record, average time, and performance history across arenas."
3. Icon: map pin — "Arena Tracking" — "See your record time and run count at every arena you've competed at."
4. Icon: bar chart — "Performance Analytics" — "Visualize trends and compare horses side-by-side to make smarter training decisions."
5. Icon: camera — "Media Gallery" — "Attach photos and videos to every run to review your form and share your best moments."
6. Icon: dollar sign — "Earnings Tracker" — "Monitor competition payouts over time to see which horses and arenas are most profitable."

---

SECTION 4 — HOW IT WORKS (id="how-it-works")

Section title: "Up and Running in Minutes"
Three numbered steps in a horizontal row with connecting dotted line between them. Each step has a large amber step number, bold title, and description.

Step 1: "Add Your Horses & Arenas" — "Build your stable and save the arenas where you compete. Takes less than 2 minutes."
Step 2: "Log Your Runs" — "After each run, enter your time, note any knocked barrels, add photos or video, and record your payout."
Step 3: "Track Your Progress" — "Watch your personal records, clean run streaks, and earnings grow over time."

Below steps: large amber CTA button "Get Started Free" linking to /app

